Heaven and Hell originally toured and recorded together as Black Sabbath from 1980-1982, and again from 1991-1992. In 2006 they reunited to record three new songs for their compilation album, Black Sabbath - The Dio Years. It was during this time that they decided to embark on a 2007-2008 tour, during which time Sabbath frontman Ozzy Osbourne was scheduled to be performing a solo tour. Because of this, and the band&#039;s entry into the Rock and Roll Hall of Fame, Iommi (who owns the name Black Sabbath) decided to call the touring group Heaven and Hell.
